## ATC/DDD Data

The Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical (ATC) classification system and Defined
Daily Dose (DDD) Index are copyright of the WHO Collaborating Centre for Drug
Statistics Methodology (Oslo, Norway).

The ATC/DDD data are freely available from the WHO Collaborating Centre's
website for non-commercial research and educational purposes. The data are
NOT distributed with this package. Users must explicitly retrieve the data
using the package's `atc_crawl()` function or download them directly from
the official source.

**Data source:** ATC/DDD Index, © WHO Collaborating Centre for Drug
Statistics Methodology. Available from <https://atcddd.fhi.no/> subject to
the provider's terms of use. The data are not distributed with this package.

Use of the ATC/DDD data is governed by the terms of use published by the
WHO Collaborating Centre at:
<https://www.whocc.no/use_of_atc_ddd/>

## Test Fixtures

Synthetic ATC codes and DDD values in `inst/extdata/synthetic_codes.csv`
and `inst/extdata/synthetic_ddd.csv` are hand-crafted test fixtures created
by the package authors. They do not contain real WHO data and are covered
by the package's MIT License.
